    "content": "# Tango Amazon ‚Äî Brain\n\n## Current Understanding\n\nAmazon is the most controllable revenue channel. Currently doing ~$3,500/mo but should be $10,000/mo. The bottleneck is **traffic** ‚Äî conversion rates are actually fine. PPC is barely running ($66 over 60 days) which is the single biggest untapped lever.\n\nTruffle is the star ‚Äî 63% of revenue. Mango's 14.7% conversion is market-rate (solved mystery ‚Äî not a problem).\n\n## What We've Learned\n\n- **Traffic is the bottleneck**, not conversion ‚Äî sessions are low, conversion is healthy\n- **PPC spend is negligible**: ~$33/mo (~$66 over 60 days) ‚Äî barely a test, let alone a campaign\n- **Truffle = 63% of revenue** ‚Äî the hero SKU, highest margin (70% on Amazon)\n- **Mango conversion (14.7%) is market-rate** ‚Äî was a mystery, now solved. Not underperforming.\n- **Amazon margins by flavor**: Truffle 70% > Sriracha 63% > Mild 55% > Thai 54% > Hot 53%\n- SD-REMARKETING campaign should be paused (from schedule notes)\n\n## Key Metrics (Jan 2026)\n\n| Metric | Current | Target |\n|--------|---------|--------|\n| Monthly revenue | $3,500 | $10,000 |\n| PPC spend | ~$33/mo | $300-600/mo |\n| Truffle % of revenue | 63% | Maintain |\n| Gap to close | $6,500/mo | ‚Äî |\n\n## Strategy\n\nThe path from $3,500 ‚Üí $10,000 is almost entirely PPC-driven:\n1. **Restart PPC at $10-20/day** ‚Äî Sponsored Products on Truffle first (highest margin hero SKU)\n2. **Analyze search term report** ‚Äî find which keywords convert, cut waste\n3. **Optimize Truffle listing** ‚Äî title, bullets, A+ content for the best-converting SKU\n4. **Scale winners** ‚Äî once ROAS is proven, increase budget\n5. **Add Sponsored Brands** ‚Äî once SP is dialed in, brand-level campaigns for cross-selling\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- What's the right PPC budget to test? $10/day? $20/day?\n- Which keywords to target for Truffle? Need search term report analysis\n- Should we run Sponsored Brands or just Sponsored Products first?\n- What's the current ACOS and ROAS on the tiny existing spend?\n- Are there any keyword rankings to protect/build on?\n- What seller fees are we actually paying? Need real number for margin calculation\n\n## Goal\n\n**This month:** Restart PPC campaigns, optimize Truffle listing, grow traffic\n**12 months:** $10,000/mo (25% of total revenue target)\n\n## Pipeline\n\n### üìã To Do\n- [ ] Restart PPC campaigns ‚Äî $10-20/day on Truffle Sponsored Products\n- [ ] Analyze search term report ‚Äî find converting keywords\n- [ ] Truffle title + bullet optimization\n- [ ] Pause SD-REMARKETING campaign\n- [ ] Fix HOTT2 listing issue (from schedule)\n- [ ] Pull current ACOS/ROAS data\n- [ ] Review A+ content for all flavors\n\n### üî® In Progress\n(none yet)\n\n### ‚úÖ Done\n- [x] Identified traffic as bottleneck (not conversion)\n- [x] Solved Mango conversion mystery (14.7% is market-rate)\n\n## Intel (Time-Sensitive)\n\n**Amazon PPC Quick Reference:**\n- Start with Sponsored Products (easiest, most data)\n- Auto campaigns first to mine keywords, then manual campaigns to target winners\n- Target ACOS: 25-35% for hot sauce category\n- Truffle should be the lead SKU (highest margin = most room for ad spend)\n- Budget $10-20/day = $300-600/mo ‚Äî still conservative but 10x current spend\n\n## Files\n\n*Located at: /Projects/üî• tango/amazon/*\n- Listings, A+ content, flat files, FNSKU labels, PPC data, screenshots\n- 1,776 files total\n",
    "summary": "Amazon is the most controllable revenue channel. Currently doing ~$3,500/mo but should be‚Ä¶",
